In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. recognizes and celebrates the contributions of public servants during Public Service Recognition Week. He acknowledges the challenges faced by America in the past year and highlights the resilience and dedication of public servants at all levels of government. These public servants include researchers, scientists, front-line workers, educators, first responders, election officials, and military service members. President Biden emphasizes that public servants are ordinary Americans who go above and beyond to make life better for all citizens, sometimes even risking their lives. He pledges to protect and empower the career Federal workforce, ensuring workplace safety during the pandemic and revoking Executive Orders that undermine civil service. President Biden also strengthens protections against discrimination for Federal employees and aims to promote a $15 per hour minimum wage for them. He concludes by calling upon all Americans to celebrate public servants and their contributions not just during this week, but throughout the year.